Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Antonio C Green not in court, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Antonio C Green.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs in court for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD.

Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 41.
Adjourned order to show cause hearing scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Antonio C Green not in court, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Antonio C Green.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Matter scheduled for State v. Lee Hearing.  Defense counsel was recently appointed and requests case be scheduled for Preliminary Hearing.  Case adjourned, Br. PE.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Antonio C Green not in court, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for a preliminary hearing. SPD has not appointed counsel. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE to the trial court for a State V. Lee Hearing.
Hearing scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Antonio C Green not in court, defendant in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is not present. SPD has not appointed counsel. Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Antonio C Green not in court, defendant in custody.  Edward OBrien appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. States witness is present. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests the matter be set for a State V. Lee hearing or status; denied.  Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 4, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with AC.; ER.;
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.   No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Antonio C Green in court with attorney Ruby De Leon.  Defendant Antonio C Green in custody.  Nate K. Mcclure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Antonio C Green appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.   Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 2 and 3. Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).   
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast: https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
